messages.message:
Patch Set 6:

This series adds several tristate (1, 0, <0) return functions. I don't object to that but when we have so many of these and I see something like:


rc = lfsck_fan_yong_check_nasf(lfsck, ...);
if (rc != 0)
        GOTO(out, rc);


Then I need to check to see if lfsck_fan_yong_check_nasf() is a tristate return function. When it's not then I wish you had written rc < 0.
